1) ANALYSIS OF THE TARGET STRUCTURE

• Block Count and Layers  
  – There are 9 total pieces.  
  – Layer‐by‐layer (bottom to top):  
    1st Layer: 4 orange cylindrical “legs.”  
    2nd Layer: 3 yellow rectangular blocks forming the “seat.”  
    3rd Layer: 1 tall green rectangular block standing vertically.  
    4th Layer: 1 yellow half‐cylinder resting on top of the green block.  

• Spatial Relationships  
  – Each of the 4 orange cylinders stands upright under the corners of the seat layer.  
  – The three flat yellow blocks span side‐by‐side to form a single seat surface.  
  – The tall green block rises from the seat’s center (toward the back edge).  
  – A yellow half‐cylinder caps the green block, curved side facing upward.

2) SELECTING DICTIONARY BLOCKS

Below are the exact dictionary blocks (no rotations allowed beyond what is shown) that match each piece:

• Legs (4×):  
  – Block #10 (orange cylinder in vertical orientation)  
• Seat (3×):  
  – Block #6 (yellow rectangular plank oriented front‐to‐back)  
• Tall Green Upright (1×):  
  – Block #2 (green rectangular prism oriented vertically)  
• Top Half‐Cylinder (1×):  
  – Block #12 (yellow half‐cylinder oriented horizontally with flat side down)

3) STEP‐BY‐STEP ASSEMBLY ORDER

{
  Step1: Move block with index 10
